conbody.p:
keyspace-name is an identifier that refers to the bucket name. It specifies
			the bucket as the source for which the index needs to be created. You can add an optional
			namespace name to the keyspace name in this way:

section.codeblock:
CREATE INDEX `beer-sample-type-index` ON `beer-sample`(type) USING GSI 
   WITH {"defer_build":true};

SELECT * FROM system:indexes WHERE name="beer-sample-type-index";
